        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thank you for the the clean, simple, well-explained PR. \r\n\r\nHowever this approach seems like the wrong direction, because this basically reinvents Vim's `t_xx` options, with an even more quirky interface (envvar-based DSL).\r\n\r\nAs discussed in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37274 supporting `$TERMINFO` is probably \"doomed\" since we are trying to get rid of terminfo, but we could instead support a `g:terminfo` dict.",
