        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Users can also create their own terminfo entries (based on an existing one but with some capabilities modified) and set TERM to that when starting nvim. No changes required for Nvim at all.\r\n\r\nIt’s kind of an obscure use case. Given it can be solved without Nvim’s involvement (and as Justin mentioned we want *less* terminfo machinery, not more), I’d personally advocate directing users to do that instead of changing Nvim.  ",
